Chet,<br><br>
Doc Del was off on a break from the site for a while, the last I knew. He said his personal situation required it. I hope he hasn't forgotten us! I miss his wit. Nurse Ratchet hasn't been around for a while either.<br><br>
I was in the south, around Saigon to the Cambodian border, north to An Loc, south along the Song Be to Bear Cat, 1st and 25th Divs. 69-70. Not a fun time. We had several 8&quot; and 175's attached to us, along with several batteries of 155's, three  batteries of 105's, and several 4.2&quot; mortar batteries. There were always a few batteries moving through that stayed a while for extra support. Cu Chi, Lai Khe, and the Thunders up HWY 13. We had a battery overrun once. Not very pretty.<br><br>
Funny, through that jarhead stuff, I think Cook really appreciated us!
